cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.DS 

This paper deals with the task of multi-document summarization, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses network methods to model texts, which suggests that it could be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the evaluation of the performance of a method, which could be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
